Hey 3G's. (Gary Gaums the Grunt),<br><br>
We had a 50cal...with a star-light mounted on it on Hill 65 and then on Hill 37 (June 1967-March 1968). A Marine used to snipe at gooks with it during operation, DeSoto (chu Lai), January-March 1967.<br>
I think he wrote a book or there's a book written about him. I haven't read it or know its title or the guys name, but a platoon from our company, either 2nd or 3rd platoon  India Company, 3/7, sometimes went out with him to provide security. He often set up on Charlie Ridge near Dai Loc or the hills around An Hoa to snipe at gooks in the old Arizona territory. I remember hearing about him but never met him.<br>
Seems like you had some great Co's.<br>
Those I served with that I knew by name are still very real and very fresh in my mind, those I didn't I regret not having taken the time to know.<br>
Sometimes you didn't want to know them, sometimes you couldn't help it.<br><br>
Hated it when a guy did a good deed for me, caused he cared. It was alright, but it just didn't seem right or out of place for a Jarhead to do. We were hard on each other, but gosh we loved each other.<br>

